Sep 14 2009 	A gem of a hotel -- highly personal excellent location great value	This hotel is a gem in the midst of more commercial hotels in the Union Square area. From the outside, it's quite unassuming and the small lobby can seem...well...quite small. However, once you've checked in and take the elevator to your floor, you'll discover a well planned hotel that maximizes its use of functional space. Each floor has its own nook where one can relax with family and friends. In fact, the first evening, the wine and cheese happy hour was overflowing with guests. We were a party of 6, and we couldn't make it through the hallway to get to the trays of food and drink. The manager, Wayne, must've seen my crestfallen face. He approached us immediately and suggested we get situated in the seating area of the floor where our rooms were located and that he'd have someone bring us some bottles of wine and snacks. Sure enough, just less than 5 minutes later, we were enjoying the wine and cheese on our own floor, away from the crowds. This was especially appreciated since we were there for a brief getaway with relatives for a family reunion and we had a lot of catching up to do. Added perks like freshly baked chocolate chip cookies waiting for us upon our return from dinner, and prompt service requests contributed to the pleasant stay. Finally, you can't beat the location of this place. We were just a block away from the hustle and bustle of Union Square. This allowed us to either walk or take public transportation to our destinations, yet the hotel also served as a quiet retreat when our itineraries got too hectic. I'd definitely stay here again for the personal service, excellent location, and great value.	
