Jul 20 2009 	Great service fantastic location the place to stay!	We had a 10 day stay here at the beginning of July, the hotel served as an ideal base for our sightseeing. We were upgraded upon arrival to a Junior Suite which was greatly appreciated (after a long journey from Glasgow via Philadelphia). The room was comfortable and a good size, though the carpet was stained in parts. The bathroom was also a good size and we were kept very well stocked with lovely Aveda toiletries. The continental breakfast was always well stocked with cereal, pastries, fruit and bread for toast. And if you need a coffee or two before you can get going, you can have as much as you like, while reading the morning paper! Hot drinks were also available thoughout the day, with kettles on each floor. The bottled water and cookies in the evening were a fantastic bonus! We only made it to the cheese and wine on a couple of occasions but everything was of a good quality once again. This hotel is situated just steps from Union Square and a short stroll from Market Street, so if you're keen on shopping, it's ideal. Westfield Shopping Centre is highly recommended. We used public transport thoughout our stay, the MUNI passes are fantastic value at $24 for 7 days, especially when you consider that one cable car ride is $5. We used the buses mostly (you can get a map from reception that shows all the routes) and found them very efficient and easily accessible from our base at Union Square.Lastly, a big thank you to all the staff for being SO helpful and efficient throughout our stay, this hotel offers a much more personal touch than any others we've stayed in before. They have lots of good tips and will happily make reservations at restaurants and on day trips on your behalf. We were even provided with a takeaway breakfast at 6am before heading to the airport on our way home. Overall, this hotel offered great value, location and service. We would definitely recommend it to other travelers, for both short and longer stays.	
