Sep 24 2008	Great Location Great Service Great Time	The Inn at Union Square made for a great base for our vacation to San Francisco. The hotel is amidst the bustle of Union Square, but inside things are fairly quiet and relaxing - a nice escape. The continental breakfast and afternoon wine and cheese reception were a real plus. The breakast is quite extensive for a &quot;continental&quot;. You can just pad down the hall in your slippers, load up a tray and take back to your room, or dine in the small sitting area on each floor. The hotel is small, with about 30 rooms over six floors. We found the staff very friendly and helpful, particularly Ken and Omar at the front desk. It's an older place, but seemed very clean and well appointed. We would definitely consider staying here again on our next vacation to San Francisco. Business travelers may also enjoy this hotel - it seems a bit more relaxed and home-like than the sterile chain hotels.	
