Nov 15 2007 	Loved the Inn!	We loved our stay at this hotel. The location is perfect - close to shopping and wonderful restaurants. There is an abundance of restaurants within walking distance of the Inn, plus the cable car is nearby. For a spectacular view of the City, try the Leatherneck Steakhouse on the 12th floor of the Marine Memorial Hotel and Club (one block from the Inn). The food, service and view are wonderful. You can go for just a drink at the bar if you don't want to dine there. If you enjoy Asian cuisine, try the E&amp;O Trading Co, within a couple of blocks of the hotel. Fun place and good food!Every evening at the Inn we enjoyed wine and cheese in the intimate gathering room just down the hall from us. It is quite charming. Continental breakfast was served there also which was very nice. Juice, coffee, tea, fresh fruit, fresh pastries, cereal, yogurt, hard boiled eggs. A very nice assortment and great start to the day. Coffee and tea are always available and sometimes cookies in the evening.We wil defintely stay at the Inn at Union Square again if our travels take us to San Francisco. The staff is very friendly, the rooms clean, comfortable and attractive. Since there are only 30 or so rooms in the hotel, it is quiet and crowd-free. It feels more like a bed and breakfast than a tradiitonal hotel. The only negative: the view from our room was a brick wall, but we spent very little time in the room anyway so it was not a problem for us. We highly recommend the Inn...a wonderful place to stay.	
